I guess it's an issue on your end. I have no issue executing it with Python 2 and Python 3. on Ubuntu 17.04 distribution

I would suggest doing the following for Python 2 or you may use pip3 for Python 3.

  • pip install --upgrade tensorflow

  • Update all dependencies which you are required for word2vec_basic.py

  • Try running it again. If you don't get success than share your OS, Tensor flow and Python log.

body:
I guess it's an issue on your end. I have no issue executing it with `Python 2` and `Python 3.` on `Ubuntu 17.04` distribution  

I would suggest doing the following for `Python 2` or you may use pip3 for `Python 3.`

-  `pip install --upgrade tensorflow` 

-   Update all dependencies which you are required for `word2vec_basic.py`

-   Try running it again. If you don't get success than share your OS, Tensor flow and Python log.
